    <div class="feature-grid fade-in delay-1" role="list">
      <div class="feature-card" role="listitem">
        <span class="feature-card-icon">📡</span>
        <span class="feature-card-tag">Dashboard</span>
        <h3>Real-Time PMO Dashboard</h3>
        <p>F# script scans every repo under <code>~/Documents/Code/</code>. CI status, open PRs, uncommitted changes, push status — refreshed every 3 minutes via launchd.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card" role="listitem">
        <span class="feature-card-icon">📐</span>
        <span class="feature-card-tag">Standards</span>
        <h3>Repo Standards Enforcement</h3>
        <p>Portfolio-wide templates enforced by a Claude skill. Same build targets, same CI, same lint commands — every project, zero variation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card" role="listitem">
        <span class="feature-card-icon">🔒</span>
        <span class="feature-card-tag">Quality</span>
        <h3>Automated Quality Gates</h3>
        <p>Lint. Type check. Format. Unit tests. Integration tests. Coverage thresholds — monotonically increasing. No soft-fail mode. Code ships clean.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card" role="listitem">
        <span class="feature-card-icon">🌿</span>
        <span class="feature-card-tag">Parallelism</span>
        <h3>Git Worktrees</h3>
        <p>Even monorepos run parallel agents. Each agent gets an isolated worktree — same repo, different path, zero conflicts. A monolith becomes multiple workstreams.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card" role="listitem">
        <span class="feature-card-icon">🎭</span>
        <span class="feature-card-tag">Orchestration</span>
        <h3>TMC — The Conductor</h3>
        <p>Too Many Cooks manages cross-project agent coordination. File locks, dependency sequencing, conflict avoidance. Agents register, lock, release.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card" role="listitem">
        <span class="feature-card-icon">🧭</span>
        <span class="feature-card-tag">Control</span>
        <h3>Your Level of Involvement</h3>
        <p>Review every commit. Or every PR. Or just check the dashboard. You operate at the altitude that suits you — all options produce shipping code.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

